1
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,680
KEEP QUIET

2
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:49,400
SURGICAL WARD

3
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:54,400
Sir.

4
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,600
Sir.

5
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,280
What are you doing here?

6
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:20,840
You're getting discharged today.
I came to help you pack.

7
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,720
Come on.

8
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,320
<i>PARADOX THINKING</i>
<i>IN CRIMINAL INVESTIGATIONS</i>

9
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,280
BY RAN FANGXU

10
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,680
Why are you reading that?

11
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,600
Just brushing up.

12
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,240
Hey.

13
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,320
Give it back.

14
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,640
I wrote that two years ago
when I didn't know any better.

15
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,280
It's all just theory.

16
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,200
That's what I used to think too.

17
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,920
But now,

18
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:59,120
your so-called theory
actually holds up in practice.

19
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,040
It's helpful.

20
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,680
By the way, sir,

21
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:08,000
what are you planning to do
after you're discharged?

22
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,640
Can I stay on
with the Criminal Department?

23
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,360
Of course.

24
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,920
You got injured on duty.

25
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,200
The team will make room for you.

26
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Then I'll stay.

27
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,680
Good.

28
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,960
What about Xiaohe?

29
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,640
I need to look after her,

30
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,240
and I have cases to crack.

31
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,680
Cases? What case?

32
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:51,200
Do you really think Xu Meng is dead?

33
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:57,280
I've been thinking. A case
that dragged on for five years,

34
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,040
and suddenly it gets wrapped up
in three days. That's way too smooth.

35
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,320
Could there be a possibility that Xu Meng

36
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:06,040
got away from Wu Shanlong a long time ago,

37
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,840
and he just left her shoes behind?

38
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:09,880
That's possible.

39
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,640
As long as we have
solid evidence and leads,

40
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:16,760
I'll go to Director Zou
and ask to reopen the case.

41
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,519
Director Zou?

42
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,720
Why him?

43
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,000
Shouldn't we report to Captain Feng?

44
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,000
Captain Feng retired last week.

45
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,360
So that means…

46
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,440
You brat.

47
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,680
Captain Ran.

48
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,000
Come on. Don't do that.

49
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,360
You,

50
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:45,320
get back to work. Don't waste time here.

51
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,520
- Go.
- About Xu Meng's case?

52
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,120
No rush.

53
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,040
I'll think it through some more.

54
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:55,760
- I'm going then.
- Go on.

55
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,280
Hurry.

56
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:17,920
FOUR MONTHS LATER, EARLY WINTER

57
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,960
The theft ring is hiding
in the urban village.

58
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,840
If we lock it down,
we can take them all in one sweep.

59
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,440
There are so few of us.

60
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,640
How are we supposed to seal it off?

61
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,840
What about the northeast corner?

62
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,280
How do we block that? You tell me.

63
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,760
Is the arrest plan ready?

64
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,920
We are working it out.

65
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:42,560
The urban-village area is complicated.

66
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:45,760
Where's Ran Fangxu?

67
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,720
He was here just now.

68
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:54,880
Captain Ran. Captain Ran.

69
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,840
Wake up.

70
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,040
Captain Ran. Director Zou is here.

71
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,120
Director Zou,

72
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,480
I pulled an all-nighter last night.
I'm so tired. Can't keep my eyes open.

73
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,520
I'm here.

74
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,560
Get out. Go wake yourself up outside.

75
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,280
Yes, sir.

76
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,360
This group of thieves
stole 1.5 million in cash

77
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:22,400
from the Railway Administration
and is hiding in the urban village.

78
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,520
The tricky part is the northeast corner.

79
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,720
In this corner, there are over
a dozen paths of all kinds

80
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,040
and plenty of hidden openings like these.

81
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,480
We've tried multiple plans,

82
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:35,520
but still can't fully block
Luandongzi's escape routes.

83
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,320
Director Zou,

84
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:47,040
should we call in armed police for backup?

85
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,160
Director Zou.

86
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,520
Leave the northeast corner to me.

87
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:08,600
- Problem solved!
- All good then!

88
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,280
- That'd be great.
- Good then.

89
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,520
If your captain is willing
to stake his life on it,

90
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,240
- then it's settled.
- Wait.

91
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,560
- Zhao Jie.
- Yes, sir.

92
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:20,280
- Put that into the plan.
- Don't.

93
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,040
Director Zou,

94
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,240
I never said I'd stake my life.

95
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,320
- Did he or not?
- He did.

96
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,360
SOLIDARITY

97
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,400
We're short one. Just waiting on you.

98
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,520
Hurry up.

99
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,760
Has Captain Ran
gone to the northeast corner?

100
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,080
He has. Don't worry.

101
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,840
So sorry. Sorry.

102
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,280
Move.

103
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,520
Stop!

104
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,440
- Cut him off over there.
- Go.

105
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,400
- Stop.
- Stop.

106
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,120
- Don't run.
- Watch out.

107
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,040
Don't run.

108
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:51,320
Two of you, go around and box him in.

109
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,640
No one is stopping me.

110
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,800
<i>He walked right into it. Easy.</i>

111
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:10,880
<i>Don't scratch my car.</i>

112
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,200
POLICE

113
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,120
Get out.

114
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,960
Out of the car.

115
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,120
Don't shoot.

116
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,520
I surrender.

117
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,320
- Take him!
- I surrender.

118
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,160
Ow!

119
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,240
Cuff him.

120
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:29,000
- Easy.
- Don't move.

121
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,360
Take him away.

122
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,120
Officer,

123
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,480
I have something to report.

124
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:35,600
I can help.

125
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:38,080
The property manager
of Yuanlongli, Qian Dajun.

126
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,440
He's bad news.

127
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,600
- Take him back for interrogation.
- Yes, sir.

128
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:42,880
- Officer! Trust me!
- Move.

129
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,240
Trust me!

130
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,880
- Move.
- Trust me!

131
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,000
I can help!

132
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,720
Captain Ran,

133
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:52,440
next time you have
something like this, call me in.

134
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,240
I don't often get to play cop like this.

135
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,680
- Thank you, Sun.
- Not at all.

136
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,120
- Appreciate it, Captain Sun.
- Of course.

137
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,480
We couldn't have
pulled this off without you.

138
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:00,640
Come.

139
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,560
- Good work.
- No problem.

140
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,600
MR. ZHANG

141
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,480
Hello, Mr. Zhang?

142
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,240
I'm so sorry, Mr. Zhang.

143
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,920
Please calm down. I'll handle it.

144
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
I'll deal with it right away.

145
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:21,400
NEIGHBORHOOD EAR CLEANING

146
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,120
CANDESARTAN TABLETS

147
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,960
Mister, are you from this neighborhood?

148
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,640
No.

149
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,320
You look familiar.

150
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:58,200
Back in 1997, I came to ask about

151
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:01,080
your brother and his daughter
who went missing.

152
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:07,240
I remember now.

153
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,080
You're that police officer.

154
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:13,000
Officer, any news about my niece?

155
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,040
It doesn't look good.

156
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:22,360
That poor girl has had a hard life.

157
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:25,920
She used to have someone
she was going to marry.

158
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,240
He was from out of town.

159
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,120
He came to Weiyang a few times.

160
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,440
He's from a decent family.

161
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,040
If they'd gotten married,

162
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,680
things might've turned out differently.

163
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,840
She had a boyfriend?

164
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,040
Why didn't you mention that before?

165
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,680
They lost touch a long time ago.

166
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,200
My brother was to blame.

167
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,280
He didn't approve of him
and wouldn't let them be together.

168
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,920
He forced them apart.

169
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,400
Do you remember his name?

170
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,760
What's the name?

171
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,640
It was something nice.

172
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,040
What's his name again?

173
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:01,240
Qiming. Wan Qiming.

174
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,120
Wan Qiming.

175
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,520
What did he look like?

176
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:11,240
Wait. I have a photo of him.

177
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,240
Let me show you.

178
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,720
This one. This one here.
The one with glasses.

179
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,240
This?

180
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,480
The man with glasses.

181
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:31,920
<i>The person who hired you,</i>
<i>what's their name?</i>

182
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,280
<i>What do they look like?</i>

183
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,400
<i>A man.</i>

184
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,600
He looks about 25 or 26.

185
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,320
Tall.

186
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,840
Wears glasses.

187
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,200
Side-parted hair.

188
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,160
<i>Looks well-mannered.</i>

189
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,000
USE WITH CARE, ECO-RECYCLE

190
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:54,600
Let's do it now.

191
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,000
Are you sure?

192
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,600
Who the heck are you?

193
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,360
Do you know who my boss is?

194
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,720
Who?

195
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,800
You.

196
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,360
Get lost.

197
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:20,720
Let's go home and have dumplings.

198
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,960
You're home.

199
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,160
My goodness.

200
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,080
- Sir.
- Green hair. Panda eyes.

201
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,480
Torn pants. A dog collar.

202
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:37,600
I'm raising a kid, not some freak.

203
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:39,680
He Yuanhang, what did you promise me?

204
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,280
If I'd known, I would've gone
to the provincial capital with my mom.

205
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,920
You think I don't keep my word?

206
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,240
I used to just be your dad.

207
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,640
Now I'm playing both parents.

208
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,000
Look at you.

209
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,840
Dye your hair today, tattoo tomorrow.

210
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,240
What's next, drugs?

211
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,920
You're a student, you know that?

212
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,960
School is for idiots.

213
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,120
I'm doing rock.

214
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,480
That's real rock spirit.

215
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,920
Rock spirit, my foot.

216
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,840
More like rock nutcase.

217
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,560
And she still has the nerve
to eat my dumplings?

218
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:20,200
What's wrong with her?
Am I pushing her too hard?

219
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,160
Take it easy.

220
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:27,640
I'm not drinking.

221
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,800
Teenagers are like this, right?

222
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,000
Anyway,

223
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:38,560
Xiaohe may be rebellious, but she's smart.

224
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:42,000
She scored over 95 in every subject
on the mock exam.

225
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,240
Her homeroom teacher told me.

226
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,640
MR. ZHANG

227
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,600
Hello, Mr. Zhang?

228
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,440
Now the teacher doesn't even know
whether to praise her

229
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,360
or scold her.

230
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,080
<i>He Xiaohe skipped school</i>
<i>five days this week.</i>

231
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:59,200
<i>Her total score didn't even reach 95.</i>

232
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:00,960
I'm so sorry, Mr. Zhang.

233
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,840
Please calm down. I'll handle it.

234
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:03,760
I'll deal with it right away.

235
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,680
Xiaohe is brain and brawn.

236
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:11,280
She might turn out to be
a great criminal investigator.

237
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,720
She's good for the physical side.

238
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,240
I've trained her myself
since she was little.

239
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:22,400
She's even better than you.

240
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,000
But academically…

241
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,840
Ninety-five in every subject?

242
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:29,840
Yeah, 95 in every subject.

243
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,440
Ninety-five in every subject…

244
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,760
Sir.

245
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,400
- Disability allowance for this month.
- I don't want it.

246
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,960
The label doesn't feel right.
Taking it feels wrong.

247
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,480
Disability allowance.

248
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:51,240
It reminds me every month
that I'm disabled.

249
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:54,240
When can I return to the team?

250
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:57,840
You're not fully recovered yet.

251
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,960
Besides, you haven't been idle.

252
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:04,400
I know you've been looking into Xu Meng.

253
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,960
I'm injured now.

254
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,560
There's nothing else I can do.

255
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,680
I might as well see this case through

256
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,720
and give myself some closure.

257
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,360
The Yuanlongli case

258
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,040
feels like it's done,

259
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,520
but not really.

260
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,480
Feels like something's
still hanging over it.

261
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,600
That's why I want to dig deeper.

262
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:47,480
I found out Xu Meng had a boyfriend

263
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,360
named Wan Qiming.

264
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:53,240
This man is suspicious.

265
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,520
I'm planning to head out of town
and meet him.

266
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:59,000
- Out of town?
- You don't have to come with me.

267
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,520
You're the captain.
You have plenty on your plate.

268
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,880
If I find anything, I'll keep you posted.

269
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,000
Captain,

270
00:17:20,079 --> 00:17:23,000
this is Luandongzi's statement.
Take a look.

271
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,680
- Did he talk?
- He did.

272
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,400
Not just that,

273
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,200
he took all the blame.

274
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:30,760
He didn't mention anything
about his accomplices.

275
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,560
We worked this hard to bring him in.

276
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:37,640
If he keeps his mouth shut,
we'll never get the others.

277
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:49,920
The cop takes out a knife.

278
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:54,960
You scared me.

279
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:58,960
Captain Ran.

280
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,000
I heard you confessed to everything.

281
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,360
Captain Ran,

282
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:27,800
well, I like coming clean. Come clean.

283
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,800
You took 1.5 million in cash
from the Railway Administration

284
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,680
all alone?

285
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,640
That's right.
I brought it out all by myself.

286
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,080
The compound is huge.

287
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:51,320
Four security teams.
Patrols every five minutes.

288
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:54,640
How did you get out
carrying all that cash?

289
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,680
I just saw my chance and took it.

290
00:18:57,760 --> 00:19:00,160
There happened to be
a heavy downpour that day.

291
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:01,680
It really covered for me.

292
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,320
Goodness.

293
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,080
Don't get worked up.

294
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:12,680
Yesterday, you shouted that you wanted
to report Qian Dajun from Yuanlongli.

295
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:13,920
What's that about?

296
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,440
I was talking nonsense.

297
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:18,920
You know my line of work.

298
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,160
High pressure.

299
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,440
Sometimes you have to let it out.

300
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,120
Come. Let's go out.

301
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,360
INTERROGATION ROOM

302
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:39,920
Let your pressure out.

303
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Take him out.

304
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,240
Didn't you hear? Let my pressure out.

305
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:48,720
Jeez. Let your pressure out?

306
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:51,440
Cops can't hit just anyone.

307
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:53,440
Hands.

308
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:01,440
Captain Ran.

309
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,760
Let's say you're telling the truth.

310
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,760
The distance from
the Railway Administration building

311
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,080
to the back gate is 1,400 meters.

312
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,920
The perimeter of this field is 86 meters.

313
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,480
Divide 1,400 by 86, it's about 16 laps.

314
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:22,480
1.5 million in cash is under 20 kilograms.

315
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:25,240
This bag of rice is 15 kilograms.

316
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,280
Here.

317
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,800
Carry it. Run 15 laps.

318
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:34,280
I'll time you. Let's see if you can
dodge patrols within five minutes.

319
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:36,320
- Wait.
- Come. I'll keep time.

320
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,120
Ready.

321
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,520
- We'll run with you.
- Ready.

322
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,520
- Listen to me.
- Run.

323
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,080
- Faster.
- Run.

324
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,880
- Pick it up.
- Move it.

325
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,240
- Speed up.
- Faster.

326
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,040
- Speed up.
- Faster.

327
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:53,000
Faster.

328
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:54,960
Keep going.

329
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,720
Speed up.

330
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,000
- Faster.
- Thank you.

331
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,400
- One minute and 30 seconds.
- Not even two minutes yet.

332
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,960
Security hasn't come around.

333
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,080
Keep running.

334
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,760
- As fast as you can.
- Get up.

335
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,800
I'll talk.

336
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:18,960
I'll tell you everything.

337
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:20,720
Not just me,

338
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:22,240
there were three others.

339
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:25,680
Including me, there were four in total.

340
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,600
Here. Wipe your face.

341
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:30,640
Thank you.

342
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:38,160
- Tell me about Qian Dajun.
- Right.

343
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:42,520
There's an underground garage
in Yuanlongli, you know?

344
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,880
That money grabber has a stash down there.

345
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:48,120
A lot of valuables.

346
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,840
Officer Ran,

347
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,760
what are you doing
in the underground garage?

348
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:58,000
<i>I saw it with my own eyes.</i>

349
00:21:58,080 --> 00:21:59,720
He carried a safe inside.

350
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,160
When he came out,

351
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:03,520
the safe was gone.

352
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:06,120
I believe something's off for sure.

353
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,480
Mr. Qian,

354
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,000
aren't you opening up slots
for rental next month?

355
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:24,080
Could you maybe squeeze us in early?

356
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:27,400
MANAGER'S OFFICE

357
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,080
CHUNGHWA CIGARETTE

358
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,960
Officer Ran. How may I help?

359
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,360
Carry on. I'll wait outside.

360
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,280
Alright.

361
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:45,600
What do you mean?

362
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,480
Cut the line? That's not happening.

363
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:50,640
The management team follows the rules.

364
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,520
Take it away. Everything.

365
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,000
- Mr. Qian.
- Remember this.

366
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:56,360
Handle everything by the book.
Open and transparent.

367
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,880
No backdoor dealings.

368
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,320
- Got it.
- Officer Ran.

369
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,920
ROAD WORK AHEAD, STAY SAFE

370
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,480
Officer Ran.

371
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:09,960
Look,

372
00:23:11,360 --> 00:23:14,320
there's nothing here. Just consumables.

373
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,320
Really. It's nothing.

374
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:27,120
All junk.

375
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,000
Officer Ran, these are just empty boxes.

376
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,360
Just…

377
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,920
Open it.

378
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,880
It's been here too long.

379
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,240
I forgot the passcode.

380
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:57,800
Forgot?

381
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,280
Then you and the boxes can come with me.

382
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,880
I remember. I remember.

383
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:05,800
I remember now.

384
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,240
Where's the thing?

385
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,640
What thing?

386
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:40,240
Qian Dajun, someone reported you
for embezzling public assets.

387
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:42,520
Officer Ran, I'm innocent.

388
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:45,160
These… These are all
discarded supplies and consumables

389
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:46,600
from the property office.

390
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,280
I just wanted to sell them off
for a little cash.

391
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:00,200
Mr. Qian,

392
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,600
a word to the wise.

393
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,600
Taking advantage can cost you big.

394
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:06,120
Yes. Right.

395
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,520
Don't worry. I'll make
all this disappear. Right away.

396
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,360
- Hello.
- Hello.

397
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:29,040
This man with glasses.

398
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:30,800
Is he a photographer here?

399
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,400
His style is unique.

400
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:35,120
He's not just the photographer,
he owns this place.

401
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,160
I see.

402
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:38,440
Is he a local?

403
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:41,520
Why are so many of his photos
taken by the sea?

404
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,560
He used to work in Guangdong.

405
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,560
Only came back last year
to open this place.

406
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,240
This one.

407
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:51,680
Guangdong's phone number.

408
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,880
Well. I'm from a magazine.

409
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:01,120
I really like his style.

410
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,960
Could I talk to him
about a possible collaboration?

411
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:06,400
Bad timing. He's out of town on a shoot.

412
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,640
I see.

413
00:27:08,200 --> 00:27:09,040
When will he be back?

414
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,120
Hard to say.

415
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:15,240
If you need this,
you can try calling his mobile.

416
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,840
But when he's out on field trips,
he usually keeps his phone off.

417
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,240
Alright. Thank you.

418
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:20,960
WAN QIMING'S BUSINESS CARD

419
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,040
Sorry.

420
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,520
This is Mr. Wan's private workspace.

421
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,200
- Not open to visitors.
- Right.

422
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,880
It does look quite unique inside.

423
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:02,600
Mr. Wan has a wide range of interests.

424
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:06,360
He collects antique knives.
He loves making specimens.

425
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:10,920
Where did he go for his field trip?

426
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:20,920
CAROUSEL'S DEAD HEAT

427
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,680
SPINNING CAROUSEL

428
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:49,680
Xiaohe.

429
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:52,320
- Xiaohe is here.
- Look who's here.

430
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,160
- Say hi.
- Officer Ran, hello.

431
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,320
Hello, guys.

432
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,040
Same as usual.
I'll pick you up in two hours.

433
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,000
You're not staying to watch the rehearsal?

434
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:04,600
I have plans. Record it.
I'll listen later at home.

435
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:09,560
You guys go ahead. Wait.

436
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:12,960
Uncle Ran, you're going on a date, right?

437
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:14,960
I saw you texting in the car just now.

438
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,520
You were blushing.

439
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:21,560
You don't show up empty-handed for a date.

440
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:28,840
Ms. Qiao will like it.

441
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:31,320
It's not that.

442
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,400
Uncle Ran, trust me.

443
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:36,560
I've watched way more dramas
than cases you've worked on.

444
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,480
Take it.

445
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:39,640
Take it.

446
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,440
Welcome.

447
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:16,160
Have you been waiting long?

448
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:18,920
I just got here.

449
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:31,200
I picked this cake up on the way just now.

450
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:32,480
It's for you.

451
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,240
Thank you.

452
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:49,480
This is

453
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:51,560
for me?

454
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:53,480
Yes.

455
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,600
It's from Xiaohe.

456
00:30:58,880 --> 00:31:00,640
I just brought it over.

457
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:10,920
Thank you.

458
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:28,640
<i>Freedom, freedom</i>

459
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:31,040
<i>It's burning</i>

460
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:34,360
<i>Close your eyes, get some rest</i>

461
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,280
<i>Run, run</i>

462
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,960
What the heck is this?

463
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,360
Who did this?

464
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,560
Come out here.

465
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,880
- Who turned on the light? Come out here.
- Come out!

466
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,040
Dad.

467
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,600
Why are you back?

468
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,200
My dear son,

469
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:56,240
you really didn't disappoint me.

470
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:57,360
Dad, let me explain.

471
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,520
Explain it to my belt.

472
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,640
- Stand right there! Stand right there!
- Dad.

473
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:01,840
- I was wrong.
- Stop!

474
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,160
- You're still running?
- Run.

475
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:04,120
Don't run.

476
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,560
Stand right there. Don't run!

477
00:32:07,560 --> 00:32:08,800
Run.

478
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,480
Not this way. The door's locked. Go.

479
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:18,120
Why are you running?

480
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:21,320
Where's the other girl?

481
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:45,360
Your guitar looks cool.

482
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:49,600
Mister, where did you get it?

483
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:51,000
You can't buy this anywhere.

484
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:04,760
<i>The summer solstice wind</i>
<i>Still blows at dusk</i>

485
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:08,360
<i>It passes the moon</i>

486
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,920
<i>Tracing the brows</i>

487
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:15,920
<i>The world under the moon is bustling</i>

488
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,160
<i>Yet I have no idea</i>

489
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:21,320
<i>Where I should go</i>

490
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:26,360
<i>Oh, youth</i>

491
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:29,160
<i>So dazzling, so vast</i>

492
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:31,800
<i>Dreams fill a young heart</i>

493
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:36,800
<i>Yet they're beyond reach</i>

494
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:47,960
Teach me that.
I'll take you as my teacher.

495
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:52,360
I'm leaving Weiyang tomorrow
for another city.

496
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:55,600
Busking? I'll go with you.

497
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:57,440
That's one man's adventure.

498
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,280
Girl,

499
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:03,520
if you really want to learn,

500
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:04,520
go to Beijing.

501
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,520
That's where rock started in China.

502
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:11,920
Beijing?

503
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,199
I'm planning to move next week

504
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:20,719
to somewhere closer to work.

505
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,400
I'm sharing a place with others.

506
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:28,080
Don't rush.

507
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:30,480
The unit just assigned me an apartment.

508
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:33,840
I'm alone and used to the dorm.
I don't need it.

509
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:36,239
If you don't mind, you can move in.

510
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,639
I can't do that.

511
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:40,600
It's assigned to you. It's not appropriate

512
00:34:40,679 --> 00:34:42,880
- for me to move in.
- It's fine.

513
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,400
You've been living alone.

514
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:47,120
You won't get used to sharing.

515
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:50,840
Thank you, Ran.

516
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:51,960
But no.

517
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,320
Honestly,

518
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,440
as long as there's no ghost,

519
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:03,080
a little discomfort

520
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,240
doesn't matter.

521
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:15,760
That old man gave me food,

522
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:17,680
money,

523
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:20,640
and a place to stay.

524
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:23,560
But

525
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:29,560
he never gave me dignity.

526
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,360
<i>He was weak and afraid of light.</i>

527
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:43,320
<i>Not a single ray of sunlight</i>
<i>was allowed inside.</i>

528
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,360
You trying to burn me?

529
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,280
<i>Back then,</i>

530
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,600
<i>I never slept well</i>

531
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,840
<i>or had a proper meal.</i>

532
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:07,800
Come here.

533
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,200
Faster.

534
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:16,720
Wipe it.

535
00:36:27,160 --> 00:36:28,280
You trollop.

536
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,000
Did you try to put me to sleep?

537
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:39,400
Did you? Did you?

538
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,840
- You want me…
- No!

539
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,280
asleep all the time?

540
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,200
Right?

541
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,520
He treated you like that.

542
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:56,000
Why did you stay and take care of him?

543
00:36:57,280 --> 00:37:00,800
He had a bad temper
and drove off every caretaker.

544
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,560
No one else would take the job.

545
00:37:03,080 --> 00:37:05,680
So the pay was high.

546
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:08,840
My mom had just passed.

547
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:11,720
I was buried in debt.

548
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:15,680
I couldn't find anything that paid better.

549
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:23,160
Qiao.

550
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:26,240
You were miserable at Yuanlongli.

551
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:27,920
After he died,

552
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:29,960
why didn't you move out?

553
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,960
His son's overseas.

554
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:35,400
He asked me to watch the place,

555
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,720
and it's rent-free.

556
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:39,560
But he's coming back soon.

557
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:44,280
Ran, I'm not trying to take advantage.

558
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:46,520
I've wanted to move out for a while.

559
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:48,240
It's just…

560
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,000
I thought maybe

561
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:03,200
I'd run into you again if I stayed there.

562
00:38:11,120 --> 00:38:13,040
Qiao, I…

563
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:18,280
Ran, don't be nervous.

564
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,680
I know I'm not good enough for you.

565
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:23,680
I… No.

566
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:27,160
That's not what I meant.

567
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:31,560
Saying this out loud

568
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:34,200
makes me feel better.

569
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:50,200
YUNSHAN ZIZHU RESTAURANT

570
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:00,560
It's cold out here. I can give you a ride.

571
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:01,880
No need.

572
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:04,560
The office is around here. I'll just walk.

573
00:39:05,080 --> 00:39:06,360
You should get back to work.

574
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,800
Hey.

575
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:14,480
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

576
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:18,600
It's okay. You don't
have to keep the flower.

577
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:20,560
No.

578
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,600
You gave it to me.

579
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:25,000
I won't let it get dirty.

580
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:13,680
Step back a bit.

581
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:14,920
The ambulance is coming.

582
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,240
Make way.

583
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:21,760
Back up.

584
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:26,480
Back up.

585
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:31,480
Look. A kid died in the fire.

586
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,800
Choked on the smoke. Didn't make it out.

587
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,640
Make way. Make way.

588
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:37,080
Make way. Ran Fangxu from Nanshan Branch.

589
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:39,320
AMBULANCE
